  </oversight_info>
  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      Following closure of surgical incisions, wounds may develop redness, swelling, and drainage
      which may result in increased pain and infection. This study will test to hypothesis that
      using the 3M TM S Surgical Skin Closure System will reduce the incidence of pain, redness,
      swelling, and infections in a group of patients undergoing a mediastinotomy incision used for
      open heart surgical procedures.
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
